On the six-month anniversary of the Capitol insurrection, President Joe Biden reflects on the attack and emphasizes the importance of protecting and preserving democracy. He acknowledges that while the event was shocking and posed a threat to democracy, it ultimately prevailed. Biden calls for unity among Democrats, Republicans, and independents to restore decency, honor, and respect for the rule of law. He also stresses the need for the government to take urgent steps to protect the right to vote. Biden concludes by expressing condolences to the families of the U.S. Capitol Police officers who lost their lives in defense of democracy and urges the nation to demonstrate its strength and goodness to the world.